"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598229","Department for Education","false","2016-10-13","<p>In July, the Secretary of State committed to introduce national funding formulae for schools and high needs from the financial year 2018-19. We will set out detailed proposals later in the autumn, and make decisions early next year, for the new system to be in place from April 2018.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-10-13T16:13:55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598229/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598229/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-10","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when the new National Funding Formula for schools will be introduced.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","47866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598230","Department for Education","false","2016-11-02","<p>The financial reporting requirements of academy trusts and maintained schools differ and therefore are not directly comparable. In the 2014/15 academic year, 113 academy trusts reported a cumulative revenue deficit in the August Accounts Return. This represents 4% of trusts submitting a return. At the end of the 2014-15 financial year, local authorities reported 944 LA-maintained schools with a deficit revenue balance. This represents 5.3% of such schools.</p><p> </p><p>Further information on the financial position of these schools can be found in the financial statements of the academy trusts or for maintained schools the Consistent Financial Reporting (CFR) returns.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-11-02T17:19:10.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598230/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598230/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598230/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-10","Schools: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of schools are currently in debt; and to whom such schools are in debt.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","47869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598231","Department for Education","false","2016-11-02","<p>The Government has protected funding for schools in real terms, so that it will rise as pupil numbers increase. However, like other public services, schools will face additional pressures in the next few years. The sources of these additional pressures are:</p><ul><li><p>Annual salary increases for staff</p></li><li><p>The introduction of the national living wage from April 2016</p></li><li><p>The increase to employer national insurance contributions from April 2016, affecting all employers who offer a defined benefit pension scheme</p></li><li><p>The increase to employer pension contributions for the Teachers’ Pension Scheme from September 2015</p></li><li><p>The introduction of the apprenticeship levy in April 2017, which will affect all employers with a paybill above £3 million</p></li><li><p>General inflation</p></li></ul><p> </p><p>Working with the sector, the Department has published a collection of tools and guidance to help school leaders, governing boards and business management professionals to improve their schools’ financial health and use their budgets more effectively. This can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/schools-financial-health-and-efficiency" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/schools-financial-health-and-efficiency</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-11-02T17:18:07.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598231/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598231/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-10-10","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent assessment she has made of the current sources of financial pressure on schools; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","47870"
