"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598431","Department of Health","false","2016-10-18","<p>The Government is undertaking work to understand in full the impacts of withdrawing from the European Union including on public health. This is ongoing and will inform the Government’s approach to future negotiations.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-18T11:04:46.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598431/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598431/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598431/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-10","European Medicines Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential (a) health and (b) economic effects of the UK withdrawing from the European Medicines Agency.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","47910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598432","Department of Health","false","2016-10-18","<p>While the people of the United Kingdom have voted to leave the European Union, until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the EU and all the rights and obligations of EU membership remain in force, including the rights associated with medical treatment abroad.</p><p>Nothing has yet been decided on the future of British citizen medical treatment abroad. Government officials are considering the positions and options available to us with the aim of achieving the best outcome for British citizens in the UK and abroad.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-18T11:03:50.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598432/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598432/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598432/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-10","Health Services: Reciprocal Arrangements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether it is the Government's policy to seek to maintain free emergency medical treatment for (a) citizens from EU countries in the UK and (b) UK citizens in EU countries after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","47914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598433","Department of Health","false","2016-10-18","<p>The safety and quality of our blood, tissue and cells and organ donation and transplant programmes must be assured. Any proposed changes within or outside Europe will continue to be considered carefully to ensure a safe and high quality service. Whilst the United Kingdom remains a full member of the European Union, EU legislation will of course continue to be in place and all obligations of EU membership will apply. Ongoing discussions are taking place regarding which rules and regulations are best placed to meet UK healthcare needs.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-18T11:07:29.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598433/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598433/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598433/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-10","Blood and Organs: Donors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether it is the Government's policy to comply with EU rules on the exchange of (a) blood and (b) organs after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","47915"
