"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595365","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Government is preparing for the UK to make an orderly and successful exit from the European Union. The Government will look to deliver its aggregate spending plans.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-10-17T16:53:09.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595365/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595365/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-07","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether it is his policy to set the extra resources needed for the Civil Service to plan, prepare and negotiate the UK's exit from the EU within the parameters of the 2015 Spending Review.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","47467"
