"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595484","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>All Government Departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules.</p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p> </p><p>More broadly, the Government will be consulting in due course on how we work with business to ensure that workers in this country have the skills that they need to get a job. But there are no proposals to publish lists of the number or proportion of foreign workers.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","47580","2016-10-17T16:45:13.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595484/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595484/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595484/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Ministry of Defence: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of staff employed by his Department are non-UK nationals.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","47411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595485","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The estate optimisation strategy aims to provide a more efficient and better quality Defence estate to support our Armed Forces, which will be fit for purpose for future generations.</p><p>This long-term, detailed work seeks to identify a rationalised Defence estate which more appropriately meets the needs of our Armed Forces by being of better quality, more cost effective and more efficient, as well as 30% smaller overall, by 2040.</p><p>No decision about the future of individual sites has been made at this point, other than those that have been previously announced</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","47195 ; 47494","2016-10-12T15:11:18.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595485/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595485/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","AAC Wattisham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has for the future military capacity of Wattisham Airbase.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","47493"
