"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595487","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-13","<p>We are not currently in a position to confirm our plans with regards to limitation. We will make an announcement in due course.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-10-13T15:05:05.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595487/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595487/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595487/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Armed Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his proposals to time-limit civil claims made in relation to military operations will apply to Operation Banner.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","47433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595488","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-14","<p>The Department is aware of the case surrounding the potential rededication of the grave for Private Anderson, but the case has not been passed to the Ministry of Defence to manage.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-10-14T12:21:07.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595488/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595488/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Netherlands: War Graves","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with his Dutch counterpart on the efforts of the Royal Netherlands Army to (a) identify and (b) mark the grave of Private Gilbert Anderson of the 11th Parachute Battalion who was killed in action on 20 September 1944.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","47352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595489","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>There are no plans to extend the provisions of the Equality Act 2010 to cover Service personnel who have dyslexia. The Defence Direction for Specific Learning Difficulties (contained within Joint Service Publication 898 'Defence Direction and Guidance on Training, Education and Skills') provides direction to all Service personnel who have dyslexia, and line managers, trainers and commanders who are required to manage Service personnel with dyslexia. It provides a learning support framework for those identified with dyslexia, ensuring that the Ministry of Defence meets its obligations as a responsible employer.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-10-12T15:13:13.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595489/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595489/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Armed Forces: Dyslexia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government plans to give people with dyslexia in the armed forces protection under the Disability Discrimination Act 1995.","false","Biography information for Kevin Foster","Torbay","Kevin Foster","47440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595490","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Ministry of Defence Police (MDP) has carried out the following investigations (taking “disturbances” to mean thefts or alleged thefts and not limited to shipwrecks) under the Protection of Military Remains Act 1986:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>YEAR</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The MDP has not received any information related to the illegal salvage of material from HMS Warrior.</p><p> </p><p>By invoking the principle of Sovereign Immunity, and by designating specific vessels under the Protection of Wrecks Act 1973 and the Protection of Military Remains Act 1986, we endeavour to protect these important sites where we are able. Where we have definitive evidence of desecration of these sites, we will take appropriate action. However, it should be appreciated that, given the large number of Royal Navy wrecks around the world and the vast area they cover, there are limitations on what can be achieved with regard to protection.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","46980 ; 46981 ; 46982 ; 47378","2016-10-12T15:07:55.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595490/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595490/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Wrecks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many reports of disturbances to military wrecks designated as protected sites under the Protection of Military Remains Act 1986 were received by the Ministry of Defence Police in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","47377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595491","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Ministry of Defence Police (MDP) has carried out the following investigations (taking “disturbances” to mean thefts or alleged thefts and not limited to shipwrecks) under the Protection of Military Remains Act 1986:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>YEAR</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The MDP has not received any information related to the illegal salvage of material from HMS Warrior.</p><p> </p><p>By invoking the principle of Sovereign Immunity, and by designating specific vessels under the Protection of Wrecks Act 1973 and the Protection of Military Remains Act 1986, we endeavour to protect these important sites where we are able. Where we have definitive evidence of desecration of these sites, we will take appropriate action. However, it should be appreciated that, given the large number of Royal Navy wrecks around the world and the vast area they cover, there are limitations on what can be achieved with regard to protection.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","46980 ; 46981 ; 46982 ; 47377","2016-10-12T15:07:55.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595491/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595491/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595491/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Wrecks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many investigations were carried out by the Ministry of Defence Police into alleged offences under the Protection of Military Remains Act 1986 in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","47378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595492","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-14","<p>Veterans UK do not routinely conduct health re-assessments once awards have been made. There are provisions under both schemes for recipients to seek a review of the level of compensation being paid.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-10-14T12:19:11.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595492/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595492/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595492/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Armed Forces Compensation Scheme and War Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to exempt people in receipt of war pensions or armed forces compensation payments from health reassessments.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","47402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595493","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-12","<p>The Ministry of Defence has received approximately 5,300 applications from veterans for the French award of the Legion d'Honneur. We have passed the majority of these to the French in accordance with the maximum permitted rate of 100 per week. We now only have 85 remaining applications to pass to the French, which will be submitted next week, and 130 applications with missing information which, therefore, cannot be processed - the Department is working to resolve these.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-12T15:21:21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595493/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595493/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/595493/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-07","Veterans: Military Decorations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Legion d'Honneur applications are outstanding in his Department.","false","Biography information for Kevin Foster","Torbay","Kevin Foster","46977"
